<subSubSection id="D89316B7A72CFFAABAAEFE03FA969AC4" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="9036453CA72CFFAABAAEFE03FE259FF0" blockId="13.[150,678,367,426]" box="[150,384,402,426]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
(
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABAA7FE03FF4B9FF0" box="[159,238,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1692,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-92@7.[151,1436,193,1644]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Adults of Scaeosopha spp. 6, S. percnaula Meyrick, lectotype ♂, Assam, India; 7, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype ♂, Bombay, India); 8, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, ♂, Hong Kong, China; 9, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Betroka, Madagascar; 10, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hainan, China; 11, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hong Kong, China." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABAC2FE03FEEB9FF0" box="[250,334,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1615,1638]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,213,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-122@12.[226,1360,195,1594]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31–34. Male genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 31, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype, genitalia slide no. JFGC7765); 32, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, genitalia slide no. ZZW08211; 33, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 32345, 33a, eighth sternum; 34, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZW09004." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">33, 33a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABB63FE03FEDD9FF0" box="[347,376,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–57" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[228,1362,212,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-76@30.[188,1398,193,1887]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 53–57. Female genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 53, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, genitalia slide no. ZZW08213; 54, S. betrokensis sp. nov., paratype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 32346; 55, S. minuta sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW002; 56, S. chionoscia Meyrick, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 31008; 57, S. rotundivalvula Li, paratype, genitalia slide no. W03106." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">54</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9036453CA72CFFAABAAFFE4BFDA89D48" blockId="13.[151,1436,474,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="A2FD992EA72CFFAABAAFFE4BFE8D9FA9" bold="true" box="[151,296,474,499]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABBBDFE4BFE6B9FA8" box="[389,462,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–11" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1692,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-92@7.[151,1436,193,1644]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 6–11. Adults of Scaeosopha spp. 6, S. percnaula Meyrick, lectotype ♂, Assam, India; 7, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype ♂, Bombay, India); 8, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, ♂, Hong Kong, China; 9, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Betroka, Madagascar; 10, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hainan, China; 11, S. hongkongensis sp. nov., holotype ♂, Hong Kong, China." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
): Wingspan 17.5–20.0 mm. Head whitish yellow. Antenna deep-yellow ringed with deep leaden. Labial palpus grayish-yellow, second segment black at base, third segment with black annulus at base and before apex. Thorax, tegula and forewing grayish-yellow, diffused with leaden scales. Forewing white with black spots on costa at base, 1/6, 1/3 and 3/5, basal one smallest, distal one semicircular and largest, extending posteriad to subcostal vein; black dots at middle of anterior margin, at 2/3 length and end of cell as well as at 3/5 length of fold, the one at end of cell rounded, and largest; a series of black dots ranging from about distal 1/4 of costal margin along termen to tornus; cilia grayish-yellow mixed with leaden. Hindwing gray; cilia gray tinged with yellow. Legs grayish-yellow; fore leg brown, fore tarsus brown and grayish-yellow on ventral surface; mid leg brown and grayish-yellow on outer side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9036453CA72CFFAABAF1FC8FFBDE9DB0" blockId="13.[151,1436,474,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABB45FC8FFDA89D6C" box="[381,525,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1615,1638]" captionTargetBox="[245,1343,213,1582]" captionTargetId="figure-122@12.[226,1360,195,1594]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 31–34. Male genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 31, S. percnaula Meyrick (= S. stagnigera Meyrick syn. nov., lectotype, genitalia slide no. JFGC7765); 32, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, genitalia slide no. ZZW08211; 33, S. betrokensis sp. nov., holotype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 32345, 33a, eighth sternum; 34, S. erecta sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. ZZW09004." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 33, 33a</figureCitation>
): Eighth sternum with a strong thorn at middle on posterior margin. Brachia of uncus setose at base, slightly expanded in distal 2/5, narrowly rounded at apex. Valva broad and short, nearly trapezoidal, widened distally; valvella shorter than valva, broad and setose at base, slightly curved downward, convex at 3/5 dorsally, distal 2/5 densely setose, gradually narrowed to roundly pointed apex. Anellus strongly sclerotized, gradually narrowed distally; apex rounded, reaching 4/5 length of tegumen, setose laterally. Phallus membranous at base; cornuti consisting of numerous longitudinal spines distally, forming a large bundle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9036453CA72CFFAABAF1FC67FA969AC4" blockId="13.[151,1436,474,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="08B259B9A72CFFAABBA5FC67FE529A54" box="[413,503,1014,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–57" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[228,1362,212,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-76@30.[188,1398,193,1887]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 53–57. Female genitalia of Scaeosopha spp. 53, S. sinevi Ponomarenko et Park, genitalia slide no. ZZW08213; 54, S. betrokensis sp. nov., paratype, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 32346; 55, S. minuta sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. ZZWGW002; 56, S. chionoscia Meyrick, BMNH Microlep. slide no. 31008; 57, S. rotundivalvula Li, paratype, genitalia slide no. W03106." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
): Posterior apophysis more than twice as long as anterior apophysis. Sterigma slightly narrowed posteriorly, anterior margin roundly convex, posterior margin slightly concave. Ductus bursae nearly same length as posterior apophysis; ductus seminalis arising from posterior end of corpus bursae. Corpus bursae large, narrow posteriorly, broad anteriorly, same length as posterior apophysis; signa paired, crescented, about 1/3 length of corpus bursae, heavily sclerotized, with numerous toothlike spinules on outer surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
